Citation.sAbstract: The (p, F, T) properties and apparent molar volumes Vo of LiCl in ethanol at T ) (298.15 to 398.15) K and  pressures up to p ) 40 MPa are reported. An empirical correlation for the density of (LiCl + C2H5OH)  with pressure, temperature, and molality has been derived. The experiments were carried out at molalities  of m ) (0.10487, 0.30229, 0.58732, 1.22211, 2.02242, and 2.87989) mol * kg-1 using lithium chloride.
Citation.sTitle: Investigations of the (p, G, T) Properties and Apparent Molar Volumes VO of the LiCl + C2H5OH Solutions
